import process
import preprocess
from sklearn.svm import SVC
from sklearn.model_selection import TimeSeriesSplit
from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestRegressor
from sklearn.naive_bayes import GaussianNB
from sklearn.neighbors import KNeighborsClassifier
from sklearn.metrics import classification_report, confusion_matrix
from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression
from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler
from sklearn.svm import SVR
import xgboost as xgb
from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression, Lasso, Ridge
from sklearn.model_selection import cross_val_score
from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
from matplotlib import pyplot as plt
import os
import warnings
warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')

plt.rcParams['figure.figsize'] = 12, 10


COMPANY = 'NVDA'
STRATEGY = 'target_class_lags_all_attributes'
# Lets try to predict stock price with pure time saries data
# read stock
INPUT_FILE = f'{COMPANY}//data//{COMPANY}_data.csv'
df = preprocess.read_data(INPUT_FILE, display=True)

# Columns: 'Date','open','high','low','close','volume','lag_1','lag_2','lag_3','lag_4','lag_5','lag_10',
# 'lag_21','lag_42','lag_63','return_1d','return_2d','return_3d','return_4d','return_5d','return_10d',
# 'return_21d','return_42d','return_63d','rsi','bb_high','bb_low','atr','macd','sma_10','sma_20','sma_50',
# 'ema_10','ema_20','ema_50','weekday_0','weekday_1','weekday_2','weekday_3','weekday_4','month_1',
# 'month_2','month_3','month_4','month_5','month_6','month_7','month_8','month_9','month_10','month_11',
# 'month_12','target_close','target_return_1d','target_class'

TARGET= 'target_class'
FEATURES = ['open','high','low','close','volume','lag_1','lag_2','lag_3','lag_4','lag_5','lag_10',
'lag_21','lag_42','lag_63','rsi','bb_high','bb_low','atr','macd','sma_10','sma_20','sma_50',
 'ema_10','ema_20','ema_50','weekday_0','weekday_1','weekday_2','weekday_3','weekday_4','month_1',
 'month_2','month_3','month_4','month_5','month_6','month_7','month_8','month_9','month_10','month_11',
 'month_12']
X, y = preprocess.preprocess_data(df, TARGET, FEATURES, True)

test_len = 260
train_end_idx = -test_len
test_start_idx = -test_len
least_train_len = 1820  # train on at least year of observations

X_train, y_train, X_test, y_test = preprocess.split_data(
    X, y, train_end_idx, test_start_idx, True)

sc = StandardScaler()
X_train_sc = sc.fit_transform(X_train)
X_test_sc = sc.transform(X_test)

#print(f'X TRAIN SCALED :: {X_train_sc}')

nr_splits = process.calculate_split_folds(X_train, least_train_len, test_len)

tscv = TimeSeriesSplit(n_splits=nr_splits, test_size=test_len)

preprocess.print_tscv(df, tscv, X_train)

SCORER = 'accuracy'
SCORE_METRICS = ['accuracy', 'f1', 'precision', 'recall', 'roc_auc']

# Logistic Regression
log_reg = LogisticRegression()
log_reg_param_grid = {'penalty':['l2'], 
              'C':[1, 10, 100, 1000]}
log_reg = process.get_gs_model_per_alg(log_reg, tscv, log_reg_param_grid, SCORER, X_train, y_train)

# Random Forest
rf = RandomForestClassifier()
rf_param_grid = { 
    'n_estimators': [200, 500],
    'max_features': ['auto', 'sqrt', 'log2'],
    'max_depth' : [4,5,6,7,8],
    'criterion' :['gini', 'entropy']
}
rf = process.get_gs_model_per_alg(rf, tscv, rf_param_grid, SCORER, X_train_sc, y_train)

# SVC
svc = SVC()
svc_param_grid = {'C': [0.1, 1, 10, 100, 1000],  
              'gamma': [1, 0.1, 0.01, 0.001, 0.0001], 
              'kernel': ['rbf']}  
svc = process.get_gs_model_per_alg(svc, tscv, svc_param_grid, SCORER, X_train_sc, y_train)

# KNN
knn = KNeighborsClassifier()
knn_param_grid = {'n_neighbors': [3,5,11,19], 
                'algorithm': ['auto', 'ball_tree', 'kd_tree', 'brute'], 
                'weights': ['uniform','distance'], 
                'metric': ['euclidean','manhattan']}  
knn = process.get_gs_model_per_alg(knn, tscv, knn_param_grid, SCORER, X_train_sc, y_train)

# Naive Bayes
gnb = GaussianNB()
gnb_param_grid = {'var_smoothing': np.logspace(0,-9, num=100)}
gnb = process.get_gs_model_per_alg(gnb, tscv, gnb_param_grid, SCORER, X_train_sc, y_train)

# Save models
models=[]
models.append(('LogReg', log_reg))
models.append(('RandomForest', rf))
models.append(('SVC', svc))
models.append(('KNN', knn))
models.append(('GNB', gnb))
  
saved_models_files = process.save_fitted_models(models, COMPANY, SCORER, test_len, STRATEGY)
print(saved_models_files)

# Choose best models
best_models=[]
best_models.append(('LogReg', log_reg.best_estimator_))
best_models.append(('RandomForest', rf.best_estimator_))
best_models.append(('SVC', svc.best_estimator_))
best_models.append(('KNN', knn.best_estimator_))
best_models.append(('GNB', gnb.best_estimator_))

def evaluate(best_models, test_len, tscv, x_train, y_train):
    df_cv_results = pd.DataFrame()
    df_feat_imp = pd.DataFrame()
    for score in SCORE_METRICS:
        print(f'SCORE :: {score}') 
        results = []
        names = [] 
        for name, best_model in best_models:
            names.append(name)
            cv_results = cross_val_score(best_model, x_train, y_train, cv=tscv, scoring=score)
            print(f'CV RESULTS: {cv_results}')
            print('%s: %f %f (%f)' % (name, cv_results.mean(),
                  np.median(cv_results), cv_results.std()))
            # Appending to file
            # result_output = f'{name} {score}:mean={cv_results.mean()} median={np.median(cv_results)} std={cv_results.std()}\n'
            cv_result_series = pd.Series({'strategy': STRATEGY, 'test_len': test_len, 'model': name, 'metric': score,
                                         'mean': cv_results.mean(), 'median': np.median(cv_results), 'std': cv_results.std()})
            df_cv_results = pd.concat(
                [df_cv_results, cv_result_series.to_frame().T], ignore_index=True)
            # with open(f"{test_len}_cv_results.txt", 'a') as file:
            #    file.write(result_output)
            results.append(cv_results)
            if ("LogReg" in name):
                imp = best_model.coef_[0]
            feat_imp_result_series = pd.Series(
                {'strategy': STRATEGY, 'test_len': test_len, 'model': name, 'metric': score, 'imp': imp})
            df_feat_imp = pd.concat(
                [df_feat_imp, feat_imp_result_series.to_frame().T], ignore_index=True)
            # with open(f"{test_len}_cv_feature_importance.txt", 'a') as f:
            #    f.write(f'{name} {score}: {imp}\n')
            print("Feature importance::", imp)
            indices = np.argsort(imp)
            plt.title(
                f'Feature Importances for {name} {score} test length {test_len}')
            plt.barh(range(len(indices)),
                     imp[indices], color='b', align='center')
            plt.yticks(range(len(indices)), [FEATURES[i] for i in indices])
            plt.show()
        plt.boxplot(results, labels=names)
        plt.title(
            f'Algorithm Comparison for score: {score} and test length: {test_len}')
        plt.show()
    cv_output_path = f"{COMPANY}//results//{COMPANY}_cv_class_results.csv"
    df_cv_results.to_csv(cv_output_path, mode='a',
                         header=not os.path.exists(cv_output_path))
    feat_output_path = f"{COMPANY}//results//{COMPANY}_class_feature_imp.csv"
    df_feat_imp.to_csv(feat_output_path, mode='a',
                       header=not os.path.exists(feat_output_path))
    return df


evaluation_results = evaluate(best_models, test_len, tscv, X_train_sc, y_train)
